<TITLE> Special traffic arrangements made for Wazed Miah's Qulkhwani on Thursday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 13 (bdnews24.com)  Qulkhwani of Dr M A Wazed Miah, atomic scientist and husband of prime minister Sheikh Hasina, will be held at the prime minister's residence on Hare Road on Thursday after Asr prayers. Special traffic arrangements have been made for the convenience of those who will be attending the function. The visitors will have to use only the Sheraton roundabout and the road in front of the chief justice's house. Male visitors will enter through the Bailey Road and female visitors through the Hare Road. All of them will leave through Bailey Road. The visitors have been requested not to bring handbags, cameras, mobile phones, electronic gadgets and umbrella, says a circular signed by prime minister's deputy press secretary Mahbubul Haque. A car-parking arrangement has been on Minto Road, Dhaka Metropolitan Police's joint commissioner, traffic, Md Jasim Uddin told bdnews24.com. Pedestrian movement can be restricted from Sheraton roundabout to the roundabout in front of the quarter of chief justice if the number of visitors increases. bdnew
